searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"Releaser","doc":"Monorepo versioning, changelog, and Hex publishing for Elixir.\n\nReleaser provides a complete toolkit for managing multi-package Elixir projects\n(poncho or umbrella). It handles version bumping with pre-release tags, cascading\nversion changes through dependency graphs, changelog generation from git commits,\nand topological publishing to Hex.","ref":"Releaser.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Features - Releaser","doc":"- **Versioning** — SemVer bump with pre-release tags (`dev`, `beta`, `rc`), cascade to dependents\n- **Publishing** — Publish all packages to Hex in dependency order, replacing `path:` deps automatically\n- **Changelog** — Generate changelogs from conventional git commits\n- **Hooks** — Pre/post-bump hooks for git tagging, changelog generation, custom logic\n- **Status** — Compare local versions against Hex to see what needs publishing","ref":"Releaser.html#module-features"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick start - Releaser","doc":"Add to your root `mix.exs`:\n\n    {:releaser, \"~> 0.1\", only: :dev, runtime: false}\n\nThen use:\n\n    mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev\n    mix releaser.graph\n    mix releaser.status\n    mix releaser.publish --dry-run","ref":"Releaser.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Releaser","doc":"Configure in your root `mix.exs` project config:\n\n    def project do\n      [\n        app: :my_project,\n        releaser: [\n          apps_root: \"apps\",\n          changelog: [anchors: %{\"feat\" => \"Added\", \"fix\" => \"Fixed\"}],\n          hooks: [post: [Releaser.Hooks.GitTag]],\n          publisher: [package_defaults: [licenses: [\"MIT\"]]]\n        ]\n      ]\n    end\n\nSee `Releaser.Config` for all options.","ref":"Releaser.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.config/0","doc":"Returns the current releaser configuration merged with defaults.","ref":"Releaser.html#config/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.App","doc":"Struct representing a discovered app in the workspace.\n\nThe `publish` field indicates whether this app should be published to Hex.\nSet `releaser: [publish: true]` in the app's `mix.exs` to mark it as publishable.","ref":"Releaser.App.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Releaser.App.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.App.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Config","doc":"Configuration schema and defaults for Releaser.\n\nAll configuration lives under the `:releaser` key in your root `mix.exs` project config.","ref":"Releaser.Config.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Options - Releaser.Config","doc":"- `:apps_root` — Root directory containing your apps. Default: `\"apps\"`\n- `:version_files` — List of `{glob_or_path, regex}` tuples for multi-file version sync\n- `:changelog` — Changelog configuration (see below)\n- `:hooks` — Pre/post hook modules (see below)\n- `:publisher` — Hex publishing configuration (see below)","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#module-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Changelog options - Releaser.Config","doc":"- `:anchors` — Map of commit prefix to changelog section.\n  Default: `%{\"feat\" => \"Added\", \"fix\" => \"Fixed\", \"refactor\" => \"Changed\", \"docs\" => \"Documentation\", \"perf\" => \"Performance\", \"breaking\" => \"Breaking Changes\"}`\n- `:path` — Path to CHANGELOG.md. Default: `\"CHANGELOG.md\"`\n- `:format` — `:keepachangelog` (default)","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#module-changelog-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Hooks options - Releaser.Config","doc":"- `:pre` — List of modules implementing `Releaser.Hooks.PreHook`\n- `:post` — List of modules implementing `Releaser.Hooks.PostHook`","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#module-hooks-options"},{"type":"module","title":"Publisher options - Releaser.Config","doc":"- `:org` — Hex organization name (optional)\n- `:package_defaults` — Default `package/0` config injected into apps that lack it.\n  Keys: `:licenses`, `:links`, `:files`","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#module-publisher-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Config.defaults/0","doc":"Returns the default configuration.","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#defaults/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Config.load/0","doc":"Loads configuration from the host project's mix.exs, merged with defaults.","ref":"Releaser.Config.html#load/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Version","doc":"SemVer version parsing, bumping, and pre-release tag management.\n\nSupports the full pre-release lifecycle:\n\n    4.0.17                          # stable\n    4.0.18-dev.1                    # first dev pre-release\n    4.0.18-dev.2                    # iterate in dev\n    4.0.18-beta.1                   # promote to beta (keeps base)\n    4.0.18-rc.1                     # release candidate\n    4.0.18                          # final release\n    4.0.18+20260420                 # with build metadata","ref":"Releaser.Version.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Tag rules - Releaser.Version","doc":"- **Clean version + tag**: bumps base, adds tag `.1` → `4.0.18-dev.1`\n- **Same tag**: only increments number → `4.0.18-dev.1` → `4.0.18-dev.2`\n- **Different tag**: keeps base, switches tag → `4.0.18-dev.3` → `4.0.18-beta.1`\n- **Release**: strips tag → `4.0.18-beta.2` → `4.0.18`","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#module-tag-rules"},{"type":"type","title":"Releaser.Version.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.base_string/1","doc":"Returns the base version string without pre-release or build metadata.","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#base_string/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.bump/3","doc":"Bumps a version by the given type (`:major`, `:minor`, `:patch`).\n\nAccepts a `%Releaser.Version{}` struct or a version string.\nWhen given a string, returns a string.","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#bump/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Releaser.Version.bump/3","doc":"- `:tag` — Pre-release tag (e.g., `\"dev\"`, `\"beta\"`, `\"rc\"`)\n- `:build` — Build metadata string (e.g., `\"20260420\"`)","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#bump/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.major_minor/1","doc":"Returns the major.minor string for Hex dependency specs.","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#major_minor/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.parse/1","doc":"Parses a version string into a `%Releaser.Version{}` struct.\n\n    iex> Releaser.Version.parse(\"4.0.18-dev.3+build.1\")\n    %Releaser.Version{major: 4, minor: 0, patch: 18, pre_tag: \"dev\", pre_num: 3, build: \"build.1\"}\n\n    iex> Releaser.Version.parse(\"1.2.3\")\n    %Releaser.Version{major: 1, minor: 2, patch: 3, pre_tag: nil, pre_num: 0, build: nil}","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#parse/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.prerelease?/1","doc":"Returns true if the version has a pre-release tag.","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#prerelease?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.release/1","doc":"Strips the pre-release tag, returning the stable base version.\n\n    iex> Releaser.Version.release(Releaser.Version.parse(\"4.0.18-beta.2\"))\n    %Releaser.Version{major: 4, minor: 0, patch: 18, pre_tag: nil, pre_num: 0, build: nil}","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#release/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Version.set/1","doc":"Sets the version to an explicit version string.\n\n    iex> Releaser.Version.set(\"2.0.0\")\n    %Releaser.Version{major: 2, minor: 0, patch: 0, pre_tag: nil, pre_num: 0, build: nil}","ref":"Releaser.Version.html#set/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Workspace","doc":"Discovers apps in a poncho/umbrella project.\n\nScans the configured `apps_root` directory for Mix projects and extracts\ntheir name, version, and internal (path-based) dependencies.\n\nSupports both flat (`apps/foo/mix.exs`) and nested (`apps/group/foo/mix.exs`) layouts.","ref":"Releaser.Workspace.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Workspace.discover/1","doc":"Discovers all apps in the workspace.\n\nReturns a list of `%Releaser.App{}` structs sorted by name.","ref":"Releaser.Workspace.html#discover/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Workspace.find/2","doc":"Finds a single app by name. Returns `nil` if not found.","ref":"Releaser.Workspace.html#find/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Cascade","doc":"Plans cascade version bumps through the dependency graph.\n\nWhen a package is bumped, all packages that depend on it receive\na patch bump automatically (like Rush in Node.js).","ref":"Releaser.Cascade.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Cascade.plan/4","doc":"Plans version changes for an app and its publishable dependents.\n\nOnly cascades to apps with `publish: true`. Non-publishable apps are\nskipped — their version in Hex (if any) is already covered by `~>` constraints.\n\nReturns a list of `%{app: name, path: path, old: version, new: version, reason: atom}`.","ref":"Releaser.Cascade.html#plan/4"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Graph","doc":"Dependency graph building and topological sorting for monorepo apps.\n\nBuilds a directed graph from internal `path:` dependencies and provides\ntopological ordering for correct publish order, dependency resolution,\nand cascade planning.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.build/1","doc":"Builds a dependency graph from a list of apps.\n\nReturns a map of `%{app_name => [dependency_names]}`.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#build/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.dependents_of/1","doc":"Returns a map of `%{app_name => [dependent_names]}` (reverse graph).\n\nFor each app, lists which apps depend on it.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#dependents_of/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.filter_levels/2","doc":"Filters topological levels to only include the specified apps.\nRemoves empty levels.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#filter_levels/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.topological_levels/1","doc":"Computes topological levels using Kahn's algorithm.\n\nReturns `[{level, [app_names]}]` where level 0 has no internal deps,\nlevel 1 depends only on level 0, etc.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#topological_levels/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.transitive_dependents/2","doc":"Resolves transitive dependents for a list of app names (reverse direction).\n\nGiven an app, returns all apps that depend on it recursively (upstream).\nFor example, if `cfdi_xml` depends on `cfdi_csd`, then `cfdi_xml` is a\ntransitive dependent of `cfdi_csd`.\n\nThis is the inverse of `transitive_deps/2`.","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#transitive_dependents/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Graph.transitive_deps/2","doc":"Resolves transitive dependencies for a list of app names.\n\nReturns a MapSet of all apps that need to be included (the requested\napps plus all their transitive dependencies).","ref":"Releaser.Graph.html#transitive_deps/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.HexStatus","doc":"Compares local app versions against published versions on Hex.\n\nUses `mix hex.info  ` to query the Hex registry.","ref":"Releaser.HexStatus.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Releaser.HexStatus.status/0","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.HexStatus.html#t:status/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.HexStatus.check/1","doc":"Checks all apps and returns their publish status.\n\nReturns a list of maps with `:app`, `:local`, `:hex`, and `:status` keys.","ref":"Releaser.HexStatus.html#check/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Publisher","doc":"Orchestrates publishing multiple apps to Hex in topological order.\n\nFor each app (in dependency order):\n1. Backs up the original `mix.exs`\n2. Replaces `path:` deps with their published Hex versions (`~> X.Y`)\n3. Injects `package/0` metadata if missing\n4. Runs `mix hex.publish --yes`\n5. Restores the original `mix.exs` (always, even on failure)","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Publisher.ensure_package_config/2","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html#ensure_package_config/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Publisher.execute/1","doc":"Executes the publish flow.","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html#execute/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Publisher.plan/1","doc":"Plans the publish order and returns a list of levels with app info.\nDoes not modify anything.","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html#plan/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Publisher.replace_path_dep/3","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html#replace_path_dep/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Publisher.restore/1","doc":"Restores backed-up mix.exs files.","ref":"Releaser.Publisher.html#restore/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Changelog","doc":"Generates changelogs from git commits using conventional commit prefixes.\n\nParses commit messages for prefixes like `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:` and\nmaps them to keepachangelog sections (Added, Fixed, Changed, etc.).","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Commit format - Releaser.Changelog","doc":"Commits should follow conventional commits:\n\n    feat: add support for CartaPorte 3.1\n    fix: correct encoding issue in XML builder\n    refactor: extract version parsing to struct\n    breaking: remove deprecated cer/key modules","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html#module-commit-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Releaser.Changelog","doc":"releaser: [\n      changelog: [\n        anchors: %{\n          \"feat\" => \"Added\",\n          \"fix\" => \"Fixed\",\n          \"refactor\" => \"Changed\",\n          \"breaking\" => \"Breaking Changes\"\n        }\n      ]\n    ]","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Changelog.generate/1","doc":"Generates a changelog string from git commits.","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html#generate/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - Releaser.Changelog.generate/1","doc":"- `:from` — Git ref to start from (default: latest tag)\n- `:to` — Git ref to end at (default: `\"HEAD\"`)\n- `:path` — Scope commits to a directory path\n- `:version` — Version string for the heading\n- `:anchors` — Map of prefix → section name (overrides config)","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html#generate/1-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Changelog.update_file/2","doc":"Reads existing CHANGELOG.md and prepends a new version entry.\n\nIf the file doesn't exist, creates it with the standard header.","ref":"Releaser.Changelog.html#update_file/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.FileSync","doc":"Syncs version numbers across multiple files.\n\nBesides `mix.exs` (which is always updated), you can configure additional\nfiles like README.md, Dockerfile, or any file containing a version string.","ref":"Releaser.FileSync.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Releaser.FileSync","doc":"releaser: [\n      version_files: [\n        {\"README.md\", ~r/version \"(+.+.+)\"/},\n        {\"Dockerfile\", ~r/ARG VERSION=(S+)/}\n      ]\n    ]","ref":"Releaser.FileSync.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.FileSync.sync_files/4","doc":"Syncs version in all configured additional files for the given app.\n\n`files` is a list of `{path_or_glob, regex}` tuples where the regex\nmust contain a capture group matching the version string to replace.","ref":"Releaser.FileSync.html#sync_files/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.FileSync.update_mix_version/3","doc":"Updates the version in `mix.exs` for the given app path.","ref":"Releaser.FileSync.html#update_mix_version/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook","doc":"Built-in post-hook that generates/updates CHANGELOG.md after a bump.\n\nUses conventional commit prefixes to categorize changes into\nkeepachangelog sections.\n\nAdd to your config:\n\n    releaser: [hooks: [post: [Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook]]]","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Hooks.GitTag","doc":"Built-in post-hook that creates a git commit and tag after bumping.\n\nStages changed `mix.exs` files, creates a commit with a descriptive message,\nand tags with the app name and version.","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.GitTag.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Commit format - Releaser.Hooks.GitTag","doc":"bump: cfdi_xml 4.0.18 → 4.0.19","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.GitTag.html#module-commit-format"},{"type":"module","title":"Tag format - Releaser.Hooks.GitTag","doc":"cfdi_xml-v4.0.19\n\nAdd to your config:\n\n    releaser: [hooks: [post: [Releaser.Hooks.GitTag]]]","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.GitTag.html#module-tag-format"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook","doc":"Behaviour for post-bump hooks.\n\nPost-hooks run after the version bump is applied. They receive a context\nmap with the results of the bump.","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Example - Releaser.Hooks.PostHook","doc":"defmodule MyProject.NotifySlack do\n      @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PostHook\n\n      @impl true\n      def run(context) do\n        # Send notification...\n        :ok\n      end\n    end\n\nThen configure:\n\n    releaser: [hooks: [post: [Releaser.Hooks.GitTag, MyProject.NotifySlack]]]","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.context/0","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.html#t:context/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.run/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PostHook.html#c:run/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook","doc":"Behaviour for pre-bump hooks.\n\nPre-hooks run before the version bump is applied. They receive a context\nmap and can abort the bump by returning `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Example - Releaser.Hooks.PreHook","doc":"defmodule MyProject.EnsureCleanTree do\n      @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PreHook\n\n      @impl true\n      def run(context) do\n        if Releaser.Git.dirty?() do\n          {:error, \"Working tree is dirty. Commit or stash your changes first.\"}\n        else\n          :ok\n        end\n      end\n    end\n\nThen configure:\n\n    releaser: [hooks: [pre: [MyProject.EnsureCleanTree]]]","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.html#module-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.context/0","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.html#t:context/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.run/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.Hooks.PreHook.html#c:run/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.Git","doc":"Git helper operations for changelog generation and post-bump hooks.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.add/1","doc":"Stages files for commit.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#add/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.commit/1","doc":"Creates a git commit with the given message.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#commit/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.dirty?/0","doc":"Returns true if the working tree has uncommitted changes.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#dirty?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.latest_tag/0","doc":"Returns the latest git tag, or nil if none.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#latest_tag/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.log/1","doc":"Returns the list of commits between two refs, optionally scoped to a path.\n\nEach commit is a map with `:hash`, `:subject`, and `:body` keys.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#log/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.Git.tag/2","doc":"Creates an annotated git tag.","ref":"Releaser.Git.html#tag/2"},{"type":"task","title":"mix releaser.bump","doc":"Bumps the semver version of an app and cascades patch bumps to dependents.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Bump.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Usage - mix releaser.bump","doc":"mix releaser.bump    \n    mix releaser.bump     --tag dev\n    mix releaser.bump   release\n    mix releaser.bump   2.0.0              # explicit version\n    mix releaser.bump --list\n    mix releaser.bump --all patch","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Bump.html#module-usage"},{"type":"task","title":"Pre-release tags - mix releaser.bump","doc":"mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev    # 4.0.17 → 4.0.18-dev.1\n    mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev    # 4.0.18-dev.1 → 4.0.18-dev.2\n    mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag beta   # 4.0.18-dev.2 → 4.0.18-beta.1\n    mix releaser.bump my_app release            # 4.0.18-beta.1 → 4.0.18","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Bump.html#module-pre-release-tags"},{"type":"task","title":"Options - mix releaser.bump","doc":"--dry-run      Show what would change without modifying files\n    --no-cascade   Only bump the specified app, skip dependents\n    --no-hooks     Skip pre/post hooks\n    --tag TAG      Pre-release tag (dev, beta, rc, alpha, etc.)\n    --build BUILD  Build metadata (e.g., 20260420)\n    --list         List all apps with current versions\n    --all TYPE     Bump all apps by the given type","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Bump.html#module-options"},{"type":"task","title":"mix releaser.changelog","doc":"Generates a changelog entry from git commits using conventional commit prefixes.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Changelog.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Usage - mix releaser.changelog","doc":"mix releaser.changelog                  # generate for all apps\n    mix releaser.changelog              # generate for one app\n    mix releaser.changelog --from v1.0.0    # from a specific git ref","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Changelog.html#module-usage"},{"type":"task","title":"Options - mix releaser.changelog","doc":"--from REF     Start from a specific git ref (default: latest tag)\n    --to REF       End at a specific git ref (default: HEAD)\n    --dry-run      Show changelog without writing to file","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Changelog.html#module-options"},{"type":"task","title":"mix releaser.graph","doc":"Displays the dependency graph of all apps in the workspace.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Graph.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Usage - mix releaser.graph","doc":"mix releaser.graph              # full graph with levels\n    mix releaser.graph          # show dependents of an app","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Graph.html#module-usage"},{"type":"task","title":"mix releaser.publish","doc":"Publishes all monorepo apps to Hex respecting the dependency graph.\n\nBefore publishing each package, `path:` dependencies are replaced with\ntheir Hex version (`~> X.Y`). After publishing (or on failure), the\noriginal `mix.exs` files are restored.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Publish.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Usage - mix releaser.publish","doc":"mix releaser.publish                    # publish all apps\n    mix releaser.publish --dry-run          # show plan without publishing\n    mix releaser.publish --only app1,app2   # only these + their deps\n    mix releaser.publish --bump patch       # bump before publishing\n    mix releaser.publish --org myorg        # publish to a Hex org","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Publish.html#module-usage"},{"type":"task","title":"Options - mix releaser.publish","doc":"--dry-run    Show publish plan without executing\n    --bump TYPE  Bump version before publishing (patch|minor|major)\n    --only APPS  Comma-separated list of apps to publish\n    --org ORG    Hex organization name","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Publish.html#module-options"},{"type":"task","title":"mix releaser.status","doc":"Shows which apps have version differences compared to what's published on Hex.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Status.html"},{"type":"task","title":"Usage - mix releaser.status","doc":"mix releaser.status","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Status.html#module-usage"},{"type":"task","title":"Output - mix releaser.status","doc":"Package              Local       Hex         Status\n    cfdi_xml             4.0.19      4.0.18      ahead\n    cfdi_csd             4.0.16      4.0.16      published\n    cfdi_complementos    4.0.18-dev.1  4.0.17    pre-release\n    my_new_app           0.1.0       —           unpublished","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Releaser.Status.html#module-output"},{"type":"module","title":"Releaser.UI","doc":"ANSI terminal output helpers for releaser mix tasks.","ref":"Releaser.UI.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.arrow/2","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#arrow/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.bright/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#bright/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.cyan/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#cyan/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.dim/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#dim/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.error/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#error/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.green/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#green/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.info/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#info/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.red/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#red/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.table_row/2","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#table_row/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Releaser.UI.yellow/1","doc":"","ref":"Releaser.UI.html#yellow/1"},{"type":"extras","title":"Releaser","doc":"# Releaser\n\nMonorepo versioning, changelog, and Hex publishing for Elixir poncho/umbrella projects.\n\nThe **only Hex package** that handles versioning + publishing for Elixir monorepos\nwith internal dependencies. Think Rush (Node.js) but for Elixir.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Features - Releaser","doc":"| Feature | Releaser | Versioce | GitHub Tag Bump |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| SemVer bump (patch/minor/major) | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n| Pre-release tags (dev, beta, rc) | Yes | Partial | Partial |\n| Same tag increments (dev.1 → dev.2) | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Tag change keeps base (dev → beta) | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Release (strip tag) | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Cascade bumps to dependents | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Dependency graph (visual) | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Topological Hex publishing | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Release status (local vs Hex) | **Yes** | No | No |\n| Changelog from git commits | Yes | Yes | No |\n| Git hooks (commit + tag) | Yes | Yes | No |\n| Multi-file version sync | Yes | Yes | No |\n| Build metadata | Yes | Yes | No |\n| Explicit version set | Yes | Yes | Yes |\n| Monorepo / poncho support | **Yes** | No | No |","ref":"readme.html#features"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - Releaser","doc":"Add to your **root** `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\ndefp deps do\n  [\n    {:releaser, \"~> 0.1\", only: :dev, runtime: false}\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Quick start - Releaser","doc":"```bash\n# List all apps and versions\nmix releaser.bump --list\n\n# See dependency graph\nmix releaser.graph\n\n# Bump a package\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch\n\n# Check what needs publishing\nmix releaser.status\n\n# Publish everything to Hex\nmix releaser.publish --dry-run\n```","ref":"readme.html#quick-start"},{"type":"extras","title":"Versioning - Releaser","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#versioning"},{"type":"extras","title":"Basic bump - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch        # 4.0.17 → 4.0.18\nmix releaser.bump my_app minor        # 4.0.17 → 4.1.0\nmix releaser.bump my_app major        # 4.0.17 → 5.0.0\n```","ref":"readme.html#basic-bump"},{"type":"extras","title":"Explicit version - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.bump my_app 2.0.0        # set to exact version\n```","ref":"readme.html#explicit-version"},{"type":"extras","title":"Build metadata - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --build 20260420    # 4.0.18+20260420\n```","ref":"readme.html#build-metadata"},{"type":"extras","title":"Bump all apps - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.bump --all patch          # bump every app\n```","ref":"readme.html#bump-all-apps"},{"type":"extras","title":"Pre-release tags - Releaser","doc":"Full lifecycle support for pre-release versions following SemVer 2.0.","ref":"readme.html#pre-release-tags"},{"type":"extras","title":"Lifecycle - Releaser","doc":"```\n  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  │                   Version lifecycle                             │\n  ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n  │                                                                 │\n  │  4.0.17 (current stable)                                        │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev                     │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-dev.1          bump base + add tag            │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev                     │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-dev.2          same tag = increment only      │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev                     │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-dev.3          another dev fix                │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag beta                    │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-beta.1         tag change = keeps base        │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag beta                    │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-beta.2         beta fix                       │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app patch --tag rc                      │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18-rc.1           release candidate              │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │    ├── releaser.bump my_app release                             │\n  │    │     → 4.0.18                strip tag = stable release     │\n  │    │                                                            │\n  │  4.0.18 (new stable)                                            │\n  │                                                                 │\n  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","ref":"readme.html#lifecycle"},{"type":"extras","title":"Tag rules - Releaser","doc":"| Situation | Command | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| Clean `4.0.17` | `patch --tag dev` | `4.0.18-dev.1` (bump + tag) |\n| Same tag `-dev.2` | `patch --tag dev` | `4.0.18-dev.3` (increment) |\n| Different tag `-dev.3` | `patch --tag beta` | `4.0.18-beta.1` (keep base) |\n| Any tag `-beta.2` | `release` | `4.0.18` (strip tag) |","ref":"readme.html#tag-rules"},{"type":"extras","title":"Available tags - Releaser","doc":"| Tag | Usage |\n|---|---|\n| `dev` | Active development, may break things |\n| `alpha` | First internal test version |\n| `beta` | Feature-complete, may have bugs |\n| `rc` | Release candidate, production-ready except bugs |\n\nSemVer ordering: `alpha < beta < dev < rc < stable`","ref":"readme.html#available-tags"},{"type":"extras","title":"Cascade bumps - Releaser","doc":"When you bump a package, all packages that depend on it automatically\nreceive a patch bump:\n\n```bash\nmix releaser.bump clir_openssl minor --dry-run\n```\n\n```\nVersion changes:\n  clir_openssl              0.0.17 → 0.1.0   (direct)\n  cfdi_csd                  4.0.16 → 4.0.17   (cascade)\n  sat_auth                  1.0.1  → 1.0.2    (cascade)\n  cfdi_xml                  4.0.18 → 4.0.19   (cascade)\n  cfdi_cancelacion          0.0.1  → 0.0.2    (cascade)\n  cfdi_descarga             0.0.1  → 0.0.2    (cascade)\n```\n\nDisable with `--no-cascade`.","ref":"readme.html#cascade-bumps"},{"type":"extras","title":"Dependency graph - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.graph\n```\n\n```\n╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║           Dependency Graph                       ║\n╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n┌── Level 0  (no internal deps) ──┐\n│   cfdi_catalogos v4.0.16\n│   clir_openssl v0.0.17\n│   saxon_he v12.5.2\n│   ... (28 apps)\n│       ▼\n┌── Level 1 ──┐\n│   cfdi_csd v4.0.16\n│   └─ depends on: clir_openssl\n│       ▼\n┌── Level 2 ──┐\n│   cfdi_xml v4.0.18\n│   └─ depends on: cfdi_csd, cfdi_transform, ...\n│   sat_auth v1.0.1\n│   └─ depends on: cfdi_csd\n│       ▼\n┌── Level 3 ──┐\n│   cfdi_cancelacion v0.0.1\n│   └─ depends on: sat_auth\n└── end ──┘\n```\n\nShow dependents of a specific app:\n\n```bash\nmix releaser.graph cfdi_csd\n```\n\n```\nDependents of cfdi_csd:\n  └─ sat_auth\n    └─ cfdi_cancelacion\n    └─ cfdi_descarga\n  └─ cfdi_xml\n```","ref":"readme.html#dependency-graph"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publishing to Hex - Releaser","doc":"Publishes all packages in topological order (dependencies first).\nAutomatically replaces `path:` deps with Hex versions and restores\nafter publishing.\n\n```bash\n# See the publish plan\nmix releaser.publish --dry-run\n\n# Publish everything\nmix releaser.publish\n\n# Bump + publish\nmix releaser.publish --bump patch\n\n# Only specific apps (+ their deps automatically)\nmix releaser.publish --only cfdi_xml\n\n# Publish to a Hex organization\nmix releaser.publish --org myorg\n```","ref":"readme.html#publishing-to-hex"},{"type":"extras","title":"What happens internally - Releaser","doc":"For each package (in dependency order):\n\n1. Backup `mix.exs`\n2. Bump version (if `--bump`)\n3. Replace `{:dep, path: \"...\"}` → `{:dep, \"~> X.Y\"}`\n4. Inject `package/0` if missing\n5. `mix hex.publish --yes`\n6. Restore original `mix.exs` (always, even on failure)","ref":"readme.html#what-happens-internally"},{"type":"extras","title":"Release status - Releaser","doc":"Compare local versions against what's published on Hex:\n\n```bash\nmix releaser.status\n```\n\n```\nPackage              Local       Hex         Status\ncfdi_xml             4.0.19      4.0.18      ahead\ncfdi_csd             4.0.16      4.0.16      published\ncfdi_complementos    4.0.18-dev.1  4.0.17    pre-release\nmy_new_app           0.1.0       —           unpublished\n\n2 package(s) need publishing.\n```","ref":"readme.html#release-status"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog - Releaser","doc":"Generate changelogs from git commits using conventional commit prefixes:\n\n```bash\n# Generate for all apps\nmix releaser.changelog\n\n# Generate for one app\nmix releaser.changelog cfdi_xml\n\n# Preview without writing\nmix releaser.changelog --dry-run\n\n# From a specific ref\nmix releaser.changelog --from v4.0.17\n```\n\nCommits should follow conventional commits:\n\n```\nfeat: add CartaPorte 3.1 support\nfix: correct XML encoding for special characters\nrefactor: extract version parsing to struct\nbreaking: remove deprecated cer/key modules\n```\n\nOutput follows [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format.","ref":"readme.html#changelog"},{"type":"extras","title":"Hooks - Releaser","doc":"Pre and post-bump hooks for custom automation.","ref":"readme.html#hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Built-in hooks - Releaser","doc":"| Hook | Type | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Releaser.Hooks.GitTag` | post | `git add` + `git commit` + `git tag` |\n| `Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook` | post | Generate/update CHANGELOG.md |","ref":"readme.html#built-in-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Custom hooks - Releaser","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyProject.NotifySlack do\n  @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PostHook\n\n  @impl true\n  def run(%{app: app, new_version: version, changes: changes}) do\n    # Send Slack notification...\n    :ok\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#custom-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Disable hooks - Releaser","doc":"```bash\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --no-hooks\n```","ref":"readme.html#disable-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuration - Releaser","doc":"All config lives in your root `mix.exs` under the `:releaser` key:\n\n```elixir\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :my_project,\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    releaser: [\n      # Root directory containing apps (default: \"apps\")\n      apps_root: \"apps\",\n\n      # Additional files to sync version in\n      version_files: [\n        {\"README.md\", ~r/@version (\\S+)/},\n        {\"Dockerfile\", ~r/ARG VERSION=(\\S+)/}\n      ],\n\n      # Changelog configuration\n      changelog: [\n        path: \"CHANGELOG.md\",\n        anchors: %{\n          \"feat\" => \"Added\",\n          \"fix\" => \"Fixed\",\n          \"refactor\" => \"Changed\",\n          \"docs\" => \"Documentation\",\n          \"perf\" => \"Performance\",\n          \"breaking\" => \"Breaking Changes\"\n        }\n      ],\n\n      # Pre/post hooks\n      hooks: [\n        pre: [],\n        post: [Releaser.Hooks.GitTag, Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook]\n      ],\n\n      # Hex publishing defaults\n      publisher: [\n        org: nil,\n        package_defaults: [\n          licenses: [\"MIT\"],\n          links: %{\"GitHub\" => \"https://github.com/me/project\"},\n          files: ~w(lib mix.exs README.md LICENSE)\n        ]\n      ]\n    ]\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#configuration"},{"type":"extras","title":"All commands - Releaser","doc":"```bash\n# Versioning\nmix releaser.bump         # bump with cascade\nmix releaser.bump     --tag dev\nmix releaser.bump   release                  # strip pre-release\nmix releaser.bump   2.0.0                    # explicit version\nmix releaser.bump --list                         # list versions\nmix releaser.bump --all patch                    # bump all apps\n\n# Graph\nmix releaser.graph                               # full dependency graph\nmix releaser.graph                           # dependents of app\n\n# Publishing\nmix releaser.publish                             # publish all to Hex\nmix releaser.publish --dry-run                   # show plan\nmix releaser.publish --only app1,app2            # only these + deps\nmix releaser.publish --bump patch                # bump before publish\nmix releaser.publish --org myorg                 # Hex organization\n\n# Status\nmix releaser.status                              # local vs Hex comparison\n\n# Changelog\nmix releaser.changelog                           # generate for all\nmix releaser.changelog                       # generate for one\nmix releaser.changelog --from v1.0.0             # from specific ref\n\n# Global options (all commands)\n--dry-run                                        # preview without changes\n--no-hooks                                       # skip pre/post hooks\n```","ref":"readme.html#all-commands"},{"type":"extras","title":"Recommended workflow - Releaser","doc":"```bash\n# 1. Start development\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev\n\n# 2. Iterate\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev          # dev.1 → dev.2\n\n# 3. Promote to beta\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag beta          # dev.3 → beta.1\n\n# 4. Release candidate\nmix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag rc\n\n# 5. Final release\nmix releaser.bump my_app release                   # rc.1 → stable\n\n# 6. Check what needs publishing\nmix releaser.status\n\n# 7. Publish\nmix releaser.publish\n```","ref":"readme.html#recommended-workflow"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - Releaser","doc":"MIT","ref":"readme.html#license"},{"type":"extras","title":"Getting Started","doc":"# Getting Started\n\nReleaser funciona con tres tipos de proyecto Elixir:\n\n1. **Poncho project** (multi-app con grupos, como cfdi-elixir)\n2. **Umbrella project** (multi-app estándar de Elixir)\n3. **Proyecto single** (un solo mix.exs sin apps/)","ref":"getting-started.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Instalación - Getting Started","doc":"Agrega `releaser` a tu **root** `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\ndefp deps do\n  [\n    {:releaser, \"~> 0.1\", only: :dev, runtime: false}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\n```bash\nmix deps.get\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#instalación"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuración por tipo de proyecto - Getting Started","doc":"","ref":"getting-started.html#configuración-por-tipo-de-proyecto"},{"type":"extras","title":"Poncho project (apps agrupados) - Getting Started","doc":"```\nmi_proyecto/\n├── mix.exs                          ← root\n├── apps/\n│   ├── cfdi/                        ← grupo\n│   │   ├── xml/mix.exs              ← app\n│   │   ├── csd/mix.exs              ← app\n│   │   └── complementos/mix.exs     ← app\n│   ├── sat/                         ← grupo\n│   │   ├── auth/mix.exs             ← app\n│   │   └── pacs/mix.exs             ← app\n│   └── clir/\n│       └── openssl/mix.exs          ← app\n```\n\nConfiguración en el root `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :mi_proyecto,\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    releaser: [\n      apps_root: \"apps\"    # default, busca mix.exs recursivamente\n    ]\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nEn cada app que quieras publicar a Hex:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/cfdi/xml/mix.exs\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :cfdi_xml,\n    version: \"4.0.18\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    description: \"XML builder para CFDI\",\n    releaser: [publish: true]         # ← marcado como publicable\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#poncho-project-apps-agrupados"},{"type":"extras","title":"Umbrella project (estándar de Elixir) - Getting Started","doc":"```\nmi_umbrella/\n├── mix.exs                          ← root umbrella\n├── apps/\n│   ├── core/mix.exs                 ← app\n│   ├── api/mix.exs                  ← app\n│   └── worker/mix.exs               ← app\n```\n\nConfiguración idéntica. Releaser detecta ambos layouts automáticamente:\n\n```elixir\n# mix.exs (root)\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :mi_umbrella,\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    apps_path: \"apps\",    # esto es de umbrella\n    deps: deps(),\n    releaser: [\n      apps_root: \"apps\"\n    ]\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nEn cada app:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/core/mix.exs\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :core,\n    version: \"1.0.0\",\n    build_path: \"../../_build\",\n    deps_path: \"../../deps\",\n    lockfile: \"../../mix.lock\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    description: \"Core business logic\",\n    releaser: [publish: true]\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#umbrella-project-estándar-de-elixir"},{"type":"extras","title":"Proyecto single (sin apps/) - Getting Started","doc":"Para un proyecto con un solo `mix.exs`:\n\n```\nmi_libreria/\n├── mix.exs\n├── lib/\n└── test/\n```\n\n```elixir\n# mix.exs\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :mi_libreria,\n    version: \"1.0.0\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    description: \"Mi librería\",\n    releaser: [\n      apps_root: \".\",           # ← apunta al directorio actual\n      publish: true\n    ]\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nEn este caso Releaser detecta un solo app y funciona para bump + changelog + publish (sin cascade porque no hay dependientes).","ref":"getting-started.html#proyecto-single-sin-apps"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publish policy - Getting Started","doc":"","ref":"getting-started.html#publish-policy"},{"type":"extras","title":"Qué es publish: true - Getting Started","doc":"El flag `releaser: [publish: true]` en el `mix.exs` de cada app controla:\n\n| Con `publish: true` | Sin `publish: true` |\n|---|---|\n| Se publica a Hex con `mix releaser.publish` | NO se publica |\n| Recibe cascade bump cuando sus deps cambian | NO recibe cascade bump |\n| Aparece en `mix releaser.publish --dry-run` | No aparece en el plan de publish |\n| Aparece en `mix releaser.status` con su estado | Aparece como \"private\" |\n| Se incluye en `mix releaser.bump --list` | Se incluye en `--list` |\n| Se incluye en `mix releaser.graph` | Se incluye en el grafo |","ref":"getting-started.html#qué-es-publish-true"},{"type":"extras","title":"Reglas de publicación - Getting Started","doc":"```\n┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       Reglas de publish                               │\n├───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                       │\n│  1. Solo apps con publish: true se publican                           │\n│                                                                       │\n│  2. Al publicar un app, también se publican sus DEPENDIENTES          │\n│     (quienes dependen de él), no sus dependencias                     │\n│                                                                       │\n│  3. Las dependencias que no son publicables (publish: false)          │\n│     se resuelven contra la versión que ya está en Hex                 │\n│                                                                       │\n│  4. El cascade de bump solo aplica a apps publicables                 │\n│                                                                       │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#reglas-de-publicación"},{"type":"extras","title":"Ejemplo: ¿qué pasa cuando modifico un app? - Getting Started","doc":"#### Caso 1: Modifico `cfdi_xml` (nadie depende de él)\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_xml patch --dry-run\n\nVersion changes:\n  cfdi_xml    4.0.18 → 4.0.19  (direct)\n  # Solo cfdi_xml — nadie más depende de él\n\n$ mix releaser.publish --only cfdi_xml --dry-run\n# Solo publica cfdi_xml\n# Sus deps (cfdi_csd, saxon_he, etc.) ya están en Hex\n```\n\n#### Caso 2: Modifico `cfdi_csd` (cfdi_xml depende de él)\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_csd patch --dry-run\n\nVersion changes:\n  cfdi_csd    4.0.16 → 4.0.17  (direct)\n  cfdi_xml    4.0.18 → 4.0.19  (cascade)  ← depende de csd, publish: true\n  # sat_auth NO aparece — tiene publish: false\n\n$ mix releaser.publish --only cfdi_csd --dry-run\n# Publica: cfdi_csd (nivel 1), luego cfdi_xml (nivel 2)\n# sat_auth NO se publica — no tiene publish: true\n```\n\n#### Caso 3: Modifico `clir_openssl` (toda la cadena depende)\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump clir_openssl patch --dry-run\n\nVersion changes:\n  clir_openssl  0.0.17 → 0.0.18  (direct)\n  cfdi_csd      4.0.16 → 4.0.17  (cascade)\n  cfdi_xml      4.0.18 → 4.0.19  (cascade)\n  # Solo los publicables cascadean\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#ejemplo-qué-pasa-cuando-modifico-un-app"},{"type":"extras","title":"Escenarios de policy - Getting Started","doc":"#### App interno que nunca se publica\n\n```elixir\n# apps/sat/scraper/mix.exs — herramienta interna de scraping\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :sat_scraper,\n    version: \"0.0.1\",\n    deps: deps()\n    # Sin releaser: [publish: true] → privado, no se publica nunca\n  ]\nend\n```\n\n#### App que YA estaba en Hex pero ya no se publicará más\n\nSi `cfdi_transform` ya está en Hex como `4.0.14` y decides no publicar más versiones:\n\n1. Quita `releaser: [publish: true]` de su `mix.exs` (o simplemente no lo pongas)\n2. La versión `4.0.14` sigue disponible en Hex\n3. Los apps que dependen de él usan `{:cfdi_transform, \"~> 4.0\"}` — resuelve a `4.0.14`\n4. No recibe cascade bumps\n5. No se intenta publicar\n\n#### App nuevo que se publicará por primera vez\n\n```elixir\n# apps/cfdi/nuevo/mix.exs\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :cfdi_nuevo,\n    version: \"0.1.0\",\n    deps: deps(),\n    description: \"Nuevo paquete\",        # requerido por Hex\n    releaser: [publish: true]\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nAl ejecutar `mix releaser.publish`, se publica por primera vez.\n`mix releaser.status` lo mostrará como \"unpublished\".","ref":"getting-started.html#escenarios-de-policy"},{"type":"extras","title":"Primeros pasos después de configurar - Getting Started","doc":"```bash\n# 1. Ver todos los apps descubiertos\n$ mix releaser.bump --list\n\n# 2. Ver el grafo de dependencias\n$ mix releaser.graph\n\n# 3. Ver qué está pendiente de publicar\n$ mix releaser.status\n\n# 4. Probar un bump (sin aplicar cambios)\n$ mix releaser.bump mi_app patch --tag dev --dry-run\n\n# 5. Probar el plan de publicación\n$ mix releaser.publish --dry-run\n```","ref":"getting-started.html#primeros-pasos-después-de-configurar"},{"type":"extras","title":"Siguiente lectura - Getting Started","doc":"- [Pre-release Tags](pre-release-tags.html) — ciclo dev → beta → rc → release\n- [Publishing to Hex](publishing-to-hex.html) — cómo funciona la publicación topológica\n- [Changelog and Hooks](changelog-and-hooks.html) — automatizar git tags y changelogs\n- [Monorepo Patterns](monorepo-patterns.html) — estructuras de proyecto y patrones avanzados","ref":"getting-started.html#siguiente-lectura"},{"type":"extras","title":"Pre-release Tags","doc":"# Pre-release Tags\n\nReleaser supports the full SemVer 2.0 pre-release lifecycle. This guide\nexplains how tags work, when to use each one, and the rules behind them.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Why pre-release tags? - Pre-release Tags","doc":"When you're developing a new feature across multiple packages, you don't\nwant to publish stable versions until everything is ready. Pre-release\ntags let you:\n\n- Publish test versions to Hex without affecting stable users\n- Iterate quickly (`dev.1 → dev.2 → dev.3`) without burning version numbers\n- Promote through stages (`dev → beta → rc → stable`) as confidence grows\n- Keep the same base version through the entire cycle","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#why-pre-release-tags"},{"type":"extras","title":"The lifecycle - Pre-release Tags","doc":"Here's a real-world example. You're adding CartaPorte 3.1 support to\n`cfdi_complementos`, currently at `4.0.17`:\n\n```bash\n# Start development — creates first dev pre-release\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag dev\n# 4.0.17 → 4.0.18-dev.1\n\n# Fixed a bug in the XSD validation, bump again\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag dev\n# 4.0.18-dev.1 → 4.0.18-dev.2\n\n# Another fix\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag dev\n# 4.0.18-dev.2 → 4.0.18-dev.3\n\n# Feature is complete, promote to beta for QA\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag beta\n# 4.0.18-dev.3 → 4.0.18-beta.1\n# Notice: base stays at 4.0.18!\n\n# QA found a bug, fix and bump\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag beta\n# 4.0.18-beta.1 → 4.0.18-beta.2\n\n# QA approved, promote to release candidate\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos patch --tag rc\n# 4.0.18-beta.2 → 4.0.18-rc.1\n\n# Everything looks good — release!\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_complementos release\n# 4.0.18-rc.1 → 4.0.18\n```\n\nThe entire cycle used a single base version: `4.0.18`.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#the-lifecycle"},{"type":"extras","title":"Rules - Pre-release Tags","doc":"There are three rules that control how tags behave:","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#rules"},{"type":"extras","title":"Rule 1: Clean version + tag = bump base + add tag - Pre-release Tags","doc":"Starting from a stable version, adding a tag bumps the base first:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev\n# 1.0.0 → 1.0.1-dev.1\n#          ^^^^^ bumped\n\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app minor --tag dev\n# 1.0.0 → 1.1.0-dev.1\n#          ^^^^^ bumped\n```\n\nThis ensures the dev version is **ahead** of the current stable.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#rule-1-clean-version-tag-bump-base-add-tag"},{"type":"extras","title":"Rule 2: Same tag = increment number only - Pre-release Tags","doc":"When you bump with the same tag, only the number increments. The base stays:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev\n# 1.0.1-dev.1 → 1.0.1-dev.2\n#                         ^ only this changes\n\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag dev\n# 1.0.1-dev.2 → 1.0.1-dev.3\n```\n\nThis is for iterating within a stage. You're not done with dev, you're\njust making more dev fixes.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#rule-2-same-tag-increment-number-only"},{"type":"extras","title":"Rule 3: Different tag = keep base, switch tag - Pre-release Tags","doc":"When you change tags (promote), the base version stays the same:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag beta\n# 1.0.1-dev.3 → 1.0.1-beta.1\n#  ^^^^^ same     ^^^^^^ new tag\n\n$ mix releaser.bump my_app patch --tag rc\n# 1.0.1-beta.2 → 1.0.1-rc.1\n#  ^^^^^ same      ^^^^ new tag\n```\n\nThis makes sense because promoting from dev to beta doesn't change the\ncode — it just changes the confidence level.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#rule-3-different-tag-keep-base-switch-tag"},{"type":"extras","title":"SemVer ordering - Pre-release Tags","doc":"Hex respects SemVer 2.0 ordering. Pre-release versions are **always less\nthan** the stable version with the same number:\n\n```\n4.0.18-alpha.1 < 4.0.18-beta.1 < 4.0.18-dev.1 < 4.0.18-rc.1 < 4.0.18\n```\n\n> Tags are ordered alphabetically: `alpha   The stable version `4.0.18` is always greater than any `4.0.18-*`.\n\nThis means users with `{:my_app, \"~> 4.0\"}` will **not** get pre-release\nversions unless they explicitly opt in with `{:my_app, \"~> 4.0.18-dev\"}`.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#semver-ordering"},{"type":"extras","title":"Common tags - Pre-release Tags","doc":"| Tag | When to use | Who installs it |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dev` | Active development, things may break | Only you and your CI |\n| `alpha` | First round of internal testing | Internal team |\n| `beta` | Feature-complete, looking for bugs | Adventurous early adopters |\n| `rc` | Release candidate, should be stable | Anyone willing to test |\n\nYou can use any string as a tag. These are just conventions.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#common-tags"},{"type":"extras","title":"With cascade - Pre-release Tags","doc":"When you bump an app with a tag, cascaded dependents get a **plain patch\nbump** (no tag). This is intentional — only the app you're actively\ndeveloping gets the pre-release tag:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_csd patch --tag dev --dry-run\n\nVersion changes:\n  cfdi_csd                  4.0.16 → 4.0.17-dev.1   (direct)\n  cfdi_xml                  4.0.18 → 4.0.19          (cascade)  ← no tag\n  sat_auth                  1.0.1  → 1.0.2           (cascade)  ← no tag\n```","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#with-cascade"},{"type":"extras","title":"With publishing - Pre-release Tags","doc":"`mix releaser.status` shows pre-release versions as a distinct status:\n\n```\nPackage              Local            Hex         Status\ncfdi_complementos    4.0.18-dev.3     4.0.17      pre-release\ncfdi_xml             4.0.19           4.0.18      ahead\n```\n\nPre-release versions are publishable to Hex but won't be installed by\ndefault by users who have `~>` version constraints.","ref":"pre-release-tags.html#with-publishing"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publishing to Hex","doc":"# Publishing to Hex\n\nThis guide explains how Releaser publishes monorepo packages to Hex in\nthe correct order, handling internal dependencies automatically.","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"The problem - Publishing to Hex","doc":"In a monorepo, packages depend on each other via `path:` references:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/api/mix.exs\ndefp deps do\n  [{:my_core, path: \"../core\"}]\nend\n```\n\nBut Hex doesn't understand `path:` — it needs version constraints:\n\n```elixir\n{:my_core, \"~> 1.1\"}\n```\n\nSo to publish `api`, you need to:\n\n1. First publish `core` to Hex\n2. Change `api`'s dep from `path:` to the published version\n3. Publish `api`\n4. Change everything back to `path:` for local development\n\nWith 34 packages and nested dependencies, doing this manually is painful.\nReleaser automates the entire process.","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#the-problem"},{"type":"extras","title":"How it works - Publishing to Hex","doc":"","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#how-it-works"},{"type":"extras","title":"Step 1: See the plan - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n$ mix releaser.publish --dry-run\n\n=== Releaser Publish ===\n\nLevel 0:\n  my_core v1.1.0\n\nLevel 1:\n  my_api v1.2.4 (deps: my_core)\n  my_worker v0.5.1 (deps: my_core)\n\n--dry-run: nothing will be published\n\nmy_api mix.exs changes:\n  {:my_core, path: \"...\"} → {:my_core, \"~> 1.1\"}\n\nmy_worker mix.exs changes:\n  {:my_core, path: \"...\"} → {:my_core, \"~> 1.1\"}\n```\n\nThis shows:\n- **Level 0**: Packages with no internal deps are published first\n- **Level 1**: Packages that depend on level 0\n- **Path replacement**: What `path:` deps become","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#step-1-see-the-plan"},{"type":"extras","title":"Step 2: Publish - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n$ mix releaser.publish\n```\n\nFor each package (in dependency order), Releaser:\n\n1. Backs up the original `mix.exs`\n2. Replaces `{:my_core, path: \"../core\"}` → `{:my_core, \"~> 1.1\"}`\n3. Injects `package/0` with license and links if missing\n4. Runs `mix hex.publish --yes`\n5. Restores the original `mix.exs`\n\nIf **any** publish fails, all `mix.exs` files are restored immediately.","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#step-2-publish"},{"type":"extras","title":"Step 3: Verify - Publishing to Hex","doc":"After publishing, your `mix.exs` files are back to using `path:` for\nlocal development. Nothing changes in your working tree.","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#step-3-verify"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publish options - Publishing to Hex","doc":"","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#publish-options"},{"type":"extras","title":"Bump before publishing - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n# Bump all packages by patch before publishing\n$ mix releaser.publish --bump patch\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#bump-before-publishing"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publish specific packages - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n# Only publish my_api (automatically includes my_core because it depends on it)\n$ mix releaser.publish --only my_api\n```\n\nThis resolves transitive dependencies: if `api` depends on `core`, and\n`core` depends on `openssl`, all three are published in the right order.","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#publish-specific-packages"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publish to a Hex organization - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n$ mix releaser.publish --org my_company\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#publish-to-a-hex-organization"},{"type":"extras","title":"Real-world example - Publishing to Hex","doc":"Here's a 34-package monorepo with 4 levels of dependencies:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.publish --dry-run\n\n=== Releaser Publish ===\n\nLevel 0:\n  cfdi_catalogos v4.0.16\n  cfdi_complementos v4.0.17\n  cfdi_transform v4.0.14\n  clir_openssl v0.0.17\n  saxon_he v12.5.2\n  ... (23 more)\n\nLevel 1:\n  cfdi_csd v4.0.16 (deps: clir_openssl)\n  cfdi_designs v1.0.0 (deps: cfdi_xml2json, cfdi_utils, cfdi_types, cfdi_complementos)\n\nLevel 2:\n  cfdi_xml v4.0.18 (deps: cfdi_csd, cfdi_transform, cfdi_complementos, cfdi_catalogos, cfdi_xsd, saxon_he)\n  sat_auth v1.0.1 (deps: cfdi_csd)\n\nLevel 3:\n  cfdi_cancelacion v0.0.1 (deps: sat_auth)\n  cfdi_descarga v0.0.1 (deps: sat_auth)\n\ncfdi_csd mix.exs changes:\n  {:clir_openssl, path: \"...\"} → {:clir_openssl, \"~> 0.0\"}\n\ncfdi_xml mix.exs changes:\n  {:cfdi_csd, path: \"...\"} → {:cfdi_csd, \"~> 4.0\"}\n  {:cfdi_transform, path: \"...\"} → {:cfdi_transform, \"~> 4.0\"}\n  {:cfdi_complementos, path: \"...\"} → {:cfdi_complementos, \"~> 4.0\"}\n  {:cfdi_catalogos, path: \"...\"} → {:cfdi_catalogos, \"~> 4.0\"}\n  {:cfdi_xsd, path: \"...\"} → {:cfdi_xsd, \"~> 4.0\"}\n  {:saxon_he, path: \"...\"} → {:saxon_he, \"~> 12.5\"}\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#real-world-example"},{"type":"extras","title":"The package/0 injection - Publishing to Hex","doc":"Many monorepo packages don't have `package/0` defined because they're not\npublished individually. Releaser automatically injects it during publish:\n\n```elixir\ndefp package do\n  [\n    licenses: [\"MIT\"],\n    links: %{\"GitHub\" => \"https://github.com/me/project\"},\n    files: ~w(lib mix.exs README.md LICENSE)\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nYou can customize the defaults in your config:\n\n```elixir\nreleaser: [\n  publisher: [\n    package_defaults: [\n      licenses: [\"Apache-2.0\"],\n      links: %{\"GitHub\" => \"https://github.com/me/project\"},\n      files: ~w(lib priv mix.exs README.md LICENSE)\n    ]\n  ]\n]\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#the-package-0-injection"},{"type":"extras","title":"Prerequisites - Publishing to Hex","doc":"- Each app must have a `description` in its `mix.exs`\n- You must be authenticated: `mix hex.user auth`\n- The app must compile without errors","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#prerequisites"},{"type":"extras","title":"Before publishing: check status - Publishing to Hex","doc":"Use `mix releaser.status` to see what needs publishing:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.status\n\n=== Release Status ===\n\nPackage              Local       Hex         Status\ncfdi_xml             4.0.19      4.0.18      ahead\ncfdi_csd             4.0.16      4.0.16      published\ncfdi_complementos    4.0.18-dev.1  4.0.17    pre-release\nmy_new_app           0.1.0       —           unpublished\n\n2 package(s) need publishing.\nRun mix releaser.publish --dry-run to see the plan.\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#before-publishing-check-status"},{"type":"extras","title":"Recommended workflow - Publishing to Hex","doc":"```bash\n# 1. Develop with pre-release tags\nmix releaser.bump cfdi_xml patch --tag dev\n# ... make changes ...\nmix releaser.bump cfdi_xml patch --tag dev\n\n# 2. When ready, release\nmix releaser.bump cfdi_xml release\n\n# 3. Check what's pending\nmix releaser.status\n\n# 4. Preview the publish plan\nmix releaser.publish --dry-run\n\n# 5. Publish\nmix releaser.publish\n```","ref":"publishing-to-hex.html#recommended-workflow"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog and Hooks","doc":"# Changelog and Hooks\n\nThis guide covers automated changelog generation and the hook system\nfor running custom logic before and after version bumps.","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changelog - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Releaser generates changelogs from git commits using\n[conventional commit](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) prefixes.","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#changelog"},{"type":"extras","title":"Commit format - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Write your commits like this:\n\n```\nfeat: add CartaPorte 3.1 complement support\nfix: correct UTF-8 encoding in XML attributes\nrefactor: extract version parsing to Version struct\ndocs: update publishing guide with org examples\nperf: cache XSD schema parsing results\nbreaking: remove deprecated cer/key modules\n```\n\nThe prefix before `:` maps to a changelog section.","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#commit-format"},{"type":"extras","title":"Default mappings - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"| Prefix | Changelog section |\n|---|---|\n| `feat` | Added |\n| `fix` | Fixed |\n| `refactor` | Changed |\n| `docs` | Documentation |\n| `perf` | Performance |\n| `breaking` | Breaking Changes |","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#default-mappings"},{"type":"extras","title":"Generate a changelog - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"```bash\n# Preview without writing\n$ mix releaser.changelog cfdi_xml --dry-run\n\nChangelog for cfdi_xml:\n\n## [4.0.19] - 2026-04-20","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#generate-a-changelog"},{"type":"extras","title":"Added - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"- add CartaPorte 3.1 complement support\n- add Certificate.toBase64() method","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#added"},{"type":"extras","title":"Fixed - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"- correct UTF-8 encoding in XML attributes","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#fixed"},{"type":"extras","title":"Changed - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"- migrate certificar() to use Certificate class\n\n--dry-run: no files written\n```\n\n```bash\n# Write to CHANGELOG.md\n$ mix releaser.changelog cfdi_xml\nUpdated apps/cfdi/xml/CHANGELOG.md\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#changed"},{"type":"extras","title":"Scope by git ref - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"```bash\n# Changes since a specific tag\n$ mix releaser.changelog cfdi_xml --from cfdi_xml-v4.0.18\n\n# Changes in a range\n$ mix releaser.changelog --from v1.0.0 --to v2.0.0\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#scope-by-git-ref"},{"type":"extras","title":"Custom anchors - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Override the default prefix → section mapping:\n\n```elixir\nreleaser: [\n  changelog: [\n    anchors: %{\n      \"feat\" => \"New Features\",\n      \"fix\" => \"Bug Fixes\",\n      \"security\" => \"Security\",\n      \"deprecate\" => \"Deprecated\",\n      \"remove\" => \"Removed\"\n    }\n  ]\n]\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#custom-anchors"},{"type":"extras","title":"Hooks - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Hooks let you run custom code before and after version bumps.","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Built-in hooks - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Releaser includes two ready-to-use hooks:\n\n#### `Releaser.Hooks.GitTag`\n\nAfter a bump, stages the changed `mix.exs` files, creates a commit, and\ntags it:\n\n```\nCommit: \"bump: version update\"\nTag:    \"cfdi_xml-v4.0.19\"\n```\n\n#### `Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook`\n\nAfter a bump, generates/updates the CHANGELOG.md in the app's directory.","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#built-in-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Enable hooks - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Add them to your config:\n\n```elixir\nreleaser: [\n  hooks: [\n    post: [\n      Releaser.Hooks.GitTag,\n      Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook\n    ]\n  ]\n]\n```\n\nNow when you bump:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_xml patch\n\nVersion changes:\n  cfdi_xml                  4.0.18 → 4.0.19   (direct)\n\n1 app(s) updated\n  changelog apps/cfdi/xml/CHANGELOG.md\n  tagged cfdi_xml-v4.0.19\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#enable-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Skip hooks for a single run - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"```bash\n$ mix releaser.bump cfdi_xml patch --no-hooks\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#skip-hooks-for-a-single-run"},{"type":"extras","title":"Writing custom hooks - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"#### Pre-hook example: ensure clean working tree\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyProject.Hooks.EnsureClean do\n  @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PreHook\n\n  @impl true\n  def run(_context) do\n    if Releaser.Git.dirty?() do\n      {:error, \"Working tree is dirty. Commit or stash changes first.\"}\n    else\n      :ok\n    end\n  end\nend\n```\n\n#### Post-hook example: notify Slack\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyProject.Hooks.NotifySlack do\n  @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PostHook\n\n  @impl true\n  def run(%{app: app, new_version: version, changes: changes}) do\n    count = length(changes)\n    message = \"Released #{app} v#{version} (#{count} package(s) updated)\"\n\n    # Your Slack API call here...\n    Slack.post_message(\"#releases\", message)\n\n    :ok\n  end\nend\n```\n\n#### Post-hook example: run tests before tagging\n\n```elixir\ndefmodule MyProject.Hooks.RunTests do\n  @behaviour Releaser.Hooks.PreHook\n\n  @impl true\n  def run(%{app: app, path: path}) do\n    case System.cmd(\"mix\", [\"test\"], cd: path, stderr_to_stdout: true) do\n      {_output, 0} -> :ok\n      {output, _} -> {:error, \"Tests failed for #{app}:\\n#{output}\"}\n    end\n  end\nend\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#writing-custom-hooks"},{"type":"extras","title":"Hook context - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"Both pre and post hooks receive a context map:\n\n```elixir\n%{\n  app: \"cfdi_xml\",                    # app being bumped\n  path: \"apps/cfdi/xml\",             # path to the app\n  old_version: \"4.0.18\",             # version before bump\n  new_version: \"4.0.19\",             # version after bump\n  bump_type: :patch,                 # :patch | :minor | :major | :release | :explicit\n  changes: [                         # all planned changes (including cascade)\n    %{app: \"cfdi_xml\", path: \"...\", old: \"4.0.18\", new: \"4.0.19\", reason: :direct},\n    %{app: \"cfdi_designs\", path: \"...\", old: \"1.0.0\", new: \"1.0.1\", reason: :cascade}\n  ],\n  apps: [%Releaser.App{}, ...]       # all discovered apps\n}\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#hook-context"},{"type":"extras","title":"Hook execution order - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"1. All pre-hooks run (in config order)\n2. If any pre-hook returns `{:error, reason}`, the bump is aborted\n3. Version files are updated\n4. All post-hooks run (in config order)\n5. If a post-hook fails, a warning is printed but the bump is not rolled back","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#hook-execution-order"},{"type":"extras","title":"Full hook configuration example - Changelog and Hooks","doc":"```elixir\nreleaser: [\n  hooks: [\n    pre: [\n      MyProject.Hooks.EnsureClean,\n      MyProject.Hooks.RunTests\n    ],\n    post: [\n      Releaser.Hooks.ChangelogHook,\n      Releaser.Hooks.GitTag,\n      MyProject.Hooks.NotifySlack\n    ]\n  ]\n]\n```","ref":"changelog-and-hooks.html#full-hook-configuration-example"},{"type":"extras","title":"Monorepo Patterns","doc":"# Monorepo Patterns\n\nPatrones de estructura, configuración y publicación para proyectos\nElixir con múltiples paquetes.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Layouts soportados - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#layouts-soportados"},{"type":"extras","title":"Umbrella (estándar de Elixir) - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\nmi_umbrella/\n├── mix.exs\n├── apps/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── mix.exs          # app: :core\n│   │   ├── lib/\n│   │   └── test/\n│   ├── api/\n│   │   ├── mix.exs          # app: :api, depends on :core\n│   │   ├── lib/\n│   │   └── test/\n│   └── worker/\n│       ├── mix.exs          # app: :worker, depends on :core\n│       ├── lib/\n│       └── test/\n```\n\nDeps entre apps:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/api/mix.exs\ndefp deps do\n  [{:core, in_umbrella: true}]      # umbrella estándar\n  # ó\n  [{:core, path: \"../core\"}]        # también funciona\nend\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#umbrella-estándar-de-elixir"},{"type":"extras","title":"Poncho (agrupado por dominio) - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\nmi_proyecto/\n├── mix.exs\n├── apps/\n│   ├── cfdi/                        ← grupo (no tiene mix.exs)\n│   │   ├── xml/mix.exs\n│   │   ├── csd/mix.exs\n│   │   └── complementos/mix.exs\n│   ├── sat/\n│   │   ├── auth/mix.exs\n│   │   └── pacs/mix.exs\n│   └── clir/\n│       ├── openssl/mix.exs\n│       └── saxon_he/mix.exs\n```\n\nDeps entre apps:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/cfdi/xml/mix.exs\ndefp deps do\n  [\n    {:cfdi_csd, path: \"../csd\"},                  # mismo grupo\n    {:saxon_he, path: \"../../clir/saxon_he\"},     # otro grupo\n    {:saxy, \"~> 1.5\"}                             # Hex externo\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#poncho-agrupado-por-dominio"},{"type":"extras","title":"Proyecto single - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\nmi_libreria/\n├── mix.exs\n├── lib/\n└── test/\n```\n\n```elixir\nreleaser: [apps_root: \".\"]\n```\n\nReleaser detecta el único `mix.exs` y funciona para bump, changelog y\npublish sin cascade (no hay dependientes).","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#proyecto-single"},{"type":"extras","title":"Publish policy - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#publish-policy"},{"type":"extras","title":"Configuración por app - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Cada app decide si es publicable con `releaser: [publish: true]` en su `mix.exs`:\n\n```elixir\n# apps/cfdi/xml/mix.exs — SE PUBLICA\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :cfdi_xml,\n    version: \"4.0.18\",\n    description: \"XML builder para CFDI\",\n    releaser: [publish: true]\n  ]\nend\n\n# apps/sat/scraper/mix.exs — NO SE PUBLICA (privado)\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :sat_scraper,\n    version: \"0.0.1\"\n    # sin releaser → privado\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#configuración-por-app"},{"type":"extras","title":"Qué controla publish: true - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\n                    ┌──────────────┬──────────────┐\n                    │ publish: true│ sin publish   │\n┌───────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤\n│ mix releaser.bump │ Recibe       │ NO recibe    │\n│ (cascade)         │ cascade bump │ cascade bump │\n├───────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤\n│ mix releaser      │ Se publica   │ NO se publica│\n│ .publish          │ a Hex        │              │\n├───────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤\n│ mix releaser      │ ahead /      │ \"private\"    │\n│ .status           │ published    │              │\n├───────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤\n│ mix releaser      │ ✓ aparece    │ ✓ aparece    │\n│ .graph            │              │              │\n├───────────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┤\n│ mix releaser.bump │ ✓ aparece    │ ✓ aparece    │\n│ --list            │              │              │\n└───────────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────┘\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#qué-controla-publish-true"},{"type":"extras","title":"Cómo se resuelven las deps al publicar - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Cuando un app publicable depende de uno no-publicable:\n\n```\ncfdi_xml (publish: true)\n  └─ depends on: cfdi_transform (NO publish)\n```\n\nAl publicar `cfdi_xml`, Releaser reemplaza:\n```elixir\n{:cfdi_transform, path: \"../transform\"}\n→\n{:cfdi_transform, \"~> 4.0\"}\n```\n\nHex resuelve `~> 4.0` contra la versión que **ya está publicada** en Hex\n(por ejemplo `4.0.14`). No intenta publicar `transform`.\n\nEsto funciona siempre que:\n1. `cfdi_transform` alguna vez se publicó a Hex, **o**\n2. `cfdi_transform` es una dep externa (ya está en Hex por otro proyecto)\n\nSi nunca se publicó y no existe en Hex, la publicación de `cfdi_xml` fallará\ncon un error de Hex diciendo que no encuentra el paquete.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#cómo-se-resuelven-las-deps-al-publicar"},{"type":"extras","title":"Dirección de cascade y publish - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\n                    DEPENDENCIAS (hacia abajo)\n                    Lo que mi app CONSUME\n                    ┌─────────────┐\n                    │ clir_openssl│  ← no se republica\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                           │\n                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │  cfdi_csd   │  ← YO MODIFIQUÉ ESTO\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                           │\n              ┌────────────┼────────────┐\n              │            │            │\n       ┌──────┴──────┐    │     ┌──────┴──────┐\n       │  cfdi_xml   │    │     │  sat_auth   │  ← solo si publish: true\n       └─────────────┘    │     └──────┬──────┘\n                          │            │\n                    DEPENDIENTES (hacia arriba)\n                    Quienes USAN mi app\n                    Se republican automáticamente\n```\n\nAl hacer `mix releaser.bump cfdi_csd patch`:\n- **Hacia abajo** (clir_openssl): NO se toca, ya está en Hex\n- **Hacia arriba** (cfdi_xml, sat_auth): cascade bump + se republican\n- Solo si tienen `publish: true`","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#dirección-de-cascade-y-publish"},{"type":"extras","title":"Flujo de dependencias entre publicables y privados - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#flujo-de-dependencias-entre-publicables-y-privados"},{"type":"extras","title":"Ejemplo real: 34 paquetes - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\n╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║ Apps publicables (publish: true)                      ║\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n║                                                       ║\n║  Level 0:  clir_openssl, cfdi_catalogos,              ║\n║            cfdi_complementos, saxon_he                 ║\n║               │                                       ║\n║  Level 1:  cfdi_csd                                   ║\n║               │                                       ║\n║  Level 2:  cfdi_xml                                   ║\n║                                                       ║\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n║ Apps privados (sin publish)                           ║\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n║                                                       ║\n║  sat_auth, sat_scraper, sat_pacs, cfdi_transform,     ║\n║  cfdi_designs, cfdi_validador, renapo_curp, ...       ║\n║                                                       ║\n║  → No se publican                                     ║\n║  → No reciben cascade                                 ║\n║  → Siguen funcionando localmente con path: deps       ║\n║                                                       ║\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#ejemplo-real-34-paquetes"},{"type":"extras","title":"Shared build paths - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Para compartir compilación entre apps (más rápido):\n\n```elixir\n# En cada app's mix.exs\ndef project do\n  [\n    app: :cfdi_xml,\n    version: \"4.0.18\",\n    build_path: \"../../../_build\",      # compartido\n    deps_path: \"../../../deps\",         # compartido\n    lockfile: \"../../../mix.lock\",      # compartido\n    deps: deps()\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nCon esto `mix compile` desde el root compila todo una vez.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#shared-build-paths"},{"type":"extras","title":"Estrategias de versionado - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#estrategias-de-versionado"},{"type":"extras","title":"Versión mayor compartida - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Todos los paquetes comparten el mismo major. Útil cuando el monorepo\nrepresenta un solo producto:\n\n```\ncfdi_xml          4.0.18\ncfdi_csd          4.0.16\ncfdi_complementos 4.0.17\nclir_openssl      4.0.12\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#versión-mayor-compartida"},{"type":"extras","title":"Versiones independientes - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Cada paquete tiene su propio ciclo. Útil cuando los paquetes son\nrealmente independientes:\n\n```\nclir_openssl      0.0.17    ← utilidad, rara vez cambia\ncfdi_xml          4.0.18    ← paquete principal\nsat_auth          1.0.1     ← API estable\n```\n\nReleaser soporta ambas. El cascade maneja la coordinación.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#versiones-independientes"},{"type":"extras","title":"Anti-patrones - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#anti-patrones"},{"type":"extras","title":"Dependencia circular - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\napp_a depends on app_b\napp_b depends on app_a     ← ERROR\n```\n\nReleaser detecta esto y muestra error. Solución: extraer la parte\ncompartida a un tercer paquete.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#dependencia-circular"},{"type":"extras","title":"App publicable que depende de uno nunca publicado - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```\ncfdi_xml (publish: true)\n  └─ depends on: mi_util_interna (never published, not in Hex)\n```\n\nAl publicar `cfdi_xml`, Hex no encontrará `mi_util_interna`. Soluciones:\n1. Publicar `mi_util_interna` primero (marcar `publish: true`)\n2. Mover el código compartido dentro de `cfdi_xml`\n3. Publicar `mi_util_interna` una vez y luego quitar `publish: true`","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#app-publicable-que-depende-de-uno-nunca-publicado"},{"type":"extras","title":"Demasiados paquetes publicables - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"Si todos los 34 paquetes son `publish: true`, cada bump cascadea a\nmuchos y cada publish toma mucho tiempo. Recomendación: solo marcar\ncomo publicables los que realmente necesitan ser consumidos\nexternamente.","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#demasiados-paquetes-publicables"},{"type":"extras","title":"Testing en monorepo - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#testing-en-monorepo"},{"type":"extras","title":"Test de un solo app - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```bash\ncd apps/cfdi/xml && mix test\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#test-de-un-solo-app"},{"type":"extras","title":"Test de todo - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"```bash\n# Desde el root\nmix test\n\n# O todos los apps con test\nfind apps -mindepth 3 -maxdepth 3 -name \"mix.exs\" -execdir mix test \\;\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#test-de-todo"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usar el grafo para CI - Monorepo Patterns","doc":"El grafo te dice el orden correcto para tests en CI:\n\n```bash\n$ mix releaser.graph\n# Level 0 → se pueden testear en paralelo (no deps internas)\n# Level 1 → testear después de level 0\n# etc.\n```","ref":"monorepo-patterns.html#usar-el-grafo-para-ci"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.1"}}